Christian McCaffrey.name: Christian McCaffrey
Christian McCaffrey.blurb: Christian McCaffrey (SF) had an elite fantasy season in 2025, averaging 24.5 PPR points across 17 games. He recorded 311 carries for 1,202 rushing yards with 10 TDs, while adding 102 receptions for 924 receiving yards and 7 TDs—totaling 2,126 yards from scrimmage and 17 total touchdowns. His best performance came in Week 7 vs ATL with 129 rushing yards, 2 TDs, and 72 receiving yards. McCaffrey exploded for 20+ points in 12 games, cementing his status as the most complete back in football. He also contributed in the playoffs with 83 rushing yards and 2 TDs across 2 games.

Puka Nacua.name: Puka Nacua
Puka Nacua.blurb: Puka Nacua (LA) delivered a historic 2025 season, averaging 23.4 PPR points across 16 games. He hauled in 129 catches for 1,715 yards and 10 TDs on 166 targets, leading the NFL in receiving through the first four weeks and flirting with a 2,000-yard pace. Nacua led the league in first downs, yards per route run, and explosive plays. His Week 16 explosion vs Seattle with 225 yards and 2 TDs was one of the best WR performances of the year. Matthew Stafford completed 24 of 25 passes to him over the middle for 311 yards, showcasing their elite chemistry.

Bijan Robinson.name: Bijan Robinson
Bijan Robinson.blurb: Bijan Robinson (ATL) delivered a historic 2025 season, leading the NFL with 2,298 yards from scrimmage—12th most in league history and a new Falcons franchise record. He rushed for 1,478 yards on 287 carries with a 5.15 YPC average and 7 TDs while adding 79 catches for 820 receiving yards. Robinson's 93-yard TD run was the longest in Falcons history, and he also broke off an 81-yard score. His spectacular campaign earned him first-team All-Pro honors and his second consecutive Pro Bowl selection. He exploded for 20+ points in 9 games.

Jahmyr Gibbs.name: Jahmyr Gibbs
Jahmyr Gibbs.blurb: Jahmyr Gibbs (DET) had an elite fantasy season in 2025 for the Lions, averaging 21.6 PPR points across 17 games. He rushed for 1,223 yards and 13 TDs (tied for 2nd in NFL) while adding 77 receptions for 616 receiving yards. His Week 12 explosion vs NYG with 55.4 fantasy points featured 219 rushing yards on 15 carries at 14.6 yards per attempt, 2 rushing TDs, plus 11 catches for 45 yards and a receiving TD in an overtime win. Gibbs ranked 4th in the league in yards per carry and earned his second consecutive Pro Bowl selection.

Josh Allen.name: Josh Allen
Josh Allen.blurb: Josh Allen (BUF) won his first NFL MVP award in 2025, beating Lamar Jackson in the closest vote since 2003. He led Buffalo to their fifth consecutive AFC East title while throwing 28 TDs with a career-low 6 interceptions and adding 12 rushing TDs. Allen became the first player in NFL history with consecutive 25+ pass TD and 12+ rush TD seasons. His Week 11 game vs TB with 42.7 fantasy points was his best performance. Allen is now one of only four active MVPs alongside Jackson, Mahomes, and Rodgers, and the third Bills MVP ever after Thurman Thomas and O.J. Simpson.
